{
  "doc_id": "42834",
  "text": "2؉ Confers Carbonate Resistance to the Lysosome/Phagosome Complex Although the above-described in vitro reactions were performed in the absence of Ca 2ϩ , several studies have come to the conclusion that elevated Ca 2ϩ concentrations correlate with fusion of lysosomes and phagosomes in intact cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, the literature on the issue is divided [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The Ca 2ϩ concentration in cytosol is usually around 100 nM but can transiently increase to micromolar levels in response to extracellular stimuli. Binding of IgGopsonized particles to Fc receptors has been shown to trigger trains of Ca 2ϩ spikes that can propagate as waves across the cell [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
